UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Gene McCANN, Defendant-Appellant. No. 280, Docket 21378. United States Court of Appeals Second Circuit. Submitted June 16, 1949. Decided July 5, 1949. Gene McCann, pro se. John F. X. McGohey, United States Attorney, New York City (John J. Donovan, Jr., Assistant United States Attorney, New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before SWAN and CHASE, Circuit Judges, and J. JOSEPH SMITH, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed.
